TITLE: The U.S. is 'certainly' still in a Covid-19 pandemic, Dr. Fauci says
SUMMARY: Dr. Anthony Fauci said the U.S. is "certainly" still in the middle of a Covid-19 pandemic, and he is "very troubled" by the divisive state of American politics.

TITLE: Democratic Sen. Raphael Warnock has big campaign cash advantage over GOP's Herschel Walker going into runoff election
SUMMARY: Sen. Raphael Warnock has almost three times more cash on hand than Republican Herschel Walker going into the runoff election.

TITLE: Sarah Palin loses election for Alaska House seat to Democratic Rep. Mary Peltola, ending comeback, NBC News projects
SUMMARY: Palin's loss was her second defeat in an election for Alaska's at-large House seat in less than three months.

TITLE: DOJ seeking to question Pence in criminal probe of Trump trying to stay in White House, report says
SUMMARY: Donald Trump is under criminal investigation by the DOJ in connection with efforts to remain in the White House after losing to President Joe Biden.

TITLE: UN report details horrifying Ukrainian accounts of abuse and torture in Russian prisons
SUMMARY: In some cases, the investigators found that Ukrainian forces tortured Russian troops, though those incidents were less frequent.

TITLE: Trump blasts Supreme Court over tax return ruling after a tough day in 3 other courts
SUMMARY: Former President Donald Trump faces a series of court cases as he seeks the 2024 Republican nomination for the White House.

TITLE: Treasury Department releases guidelines for Russian oil transport ahead of planned price cap
SUMMARY: The Treasury Department released guidance on the safe transport of oil of Russian origin before the price gap on the product activates on Dec. 5.

TITLE: Michigan man arrested in threats to FBI Director Chris Wray, Rep. Garamendi
SUMMARY: FBI Director Christopher Wray and Rep. John Garamendi, a California Democrat, allegedly were threatened by a man whose family said he has a mental illness.

TITLE: Supreme Court clears way for Trump tax records to be sent to Congress by IRS
SUMMARY: The House Ways and Means Committee for three years had sought to obtain income tax returns of former President Donald Trump.

TITLE: Trump would beat DeSantis in 2024, as Biden approval rate remains underwater, new poll finds
SUMMARY: Donald Trump holds a 30 percentage point lead over his potential GOP primary opponent, Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis, according to new poll findings.

TITLE: Iran says 40 foreigners arrested for taking part in anti-government protests
SUMMARY: Iran's judiciary spokesperson reportedly said Tuesday that 40 foreign nationals have been detained for participating in anti-regime protests.

TITLE: Gisele Fetterman, wife of Pennsylvania Sen.-elect John Fetterman, blasts right-wing 'hate' of her and other 'strong women'
SUMMARY: Gisele Fetterman acted as a spokeswoman for John Fetterman after his stroke during a Senate race in Pennsylvania against Trump-backed Republican Dr. Mehmet Oz.

TITLE: Biden pardons Thanksgiving turkeys, quips only 'red wave' will be spilled cranberry sauce —  not Republican election wins
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden made a crack at Republicans at the traditional White House ceremony to pardon Thanksgiving turkeys.

TITLE: South Carolina Supreme Court agrees to hear appeal by former Trump White House aide Mark Meadows to block grand jury subpoena
SUMMARY: A Georgia grand jury is investigating possible crimes related to efforts by Donald Trump and others to overturn the 2020 election of President Joe Biden.

TITLE: Elon Musk says he will reinstate Twitter account of former President Donald Trump after online poll
SUMMARY: Elon Musk says he will reinstate Twitter account of former President Donald Trump

TITLE: Supreme Court leaked landmark case years before Roe was overturned, ex-abortion activist says in new report
SUMMARY: A former anti-abortion leader claims he was told the outcome of a 2014 case weeks before it was announced publicly, according to a report from The New York Times.

TITLE: White House on Taylor Swift Ticketmaster debacle: Capitalism without competition is exploitation
SUMMARY: Jean-Pierre declined to comment on "any potential investigation" by the DOJ, but said the president has been clear on how he feels about monopolies.

TITLE: GOP operative convicted of funneling Russian donation to Trump's 2016 campaign
SUMMARY: A GOP political operative was convicted of funneling $25,000 from a Russian businessman to Donald Trump's 2016 presidential campaign.

TITLE: Democrat Frisch concedes to MAGA Republican Boebert in tight race for Colorado House seat
SUMMARY: Boebert's win is by the narrowest of margins. She leads Frisch by just over 500 votes, or 0.2 percentage points, with 99% of the vote in as of Friday.

TITLE: Watch live: U.S. Attorney General Merrick Garland names Trump special counsel for criminal probes
SUMMARY: The announcement comes days after Donald Trump said he would again seek election in 2024, potentially against incumbent President Joe Biden.

TITLE: Attorney General Merrick Garland names Jack Smith special counsel in Trump criminal probes
SUMMARY: Donald Trump faces multiple criminal investigations. A special counsel will be named to determine if federal charges should be lodged against the Republican.

TITLE: Biden administration asks Supreme Court to allow student debt forgiveness plan to continue
SUMMARY: The Biden administration asked the Supreme Court on Friday to lift an injunction on its student loan forgiveness plan.

TITLE: GOP megadonor Mercer family has no plans to boost Trump's 2024 campaign as former president loses more allies
SUMMARY: Republican megadonors Robert Mercer and Rebekah Mercer have no plans to help Donald Trump's 2024 campaign after spending millions to get him elected in 2016.

TITLE: Florida no longer looks like a swing state after DeSantis, Rubio lead big Republican wins
SUMMARY: Gov. Ron DeSantis and former President Donald Trump call Florida home, and unlike in most of the country, more Latino voters in Florida voted Republican.

TITLE: Children's hospitals call on Biden to declare emergency in response to 'unprecedented' RSV surge
SUMMARY: Infants 6 months and younger are getting hospitalized with RSV at seven times the rate observed before the Covid-19 pandemic, according to CDC data.

TITLE: Republicans take control of the House, NBC News projects
SUMMARY: Republicans will take majority control of the House, ousting Democrats from key positions of power and complicating President Joe Biden's legislative goals.

TITLE: Democrats will keep control of the Senate, NBC News projects
SUMMARY: Democrats will retain control of the Senate in the 2022 midterm elections, NBC News projected.

TITLE: Brits face sharpest fall in living standards on record as government tightens its belt
SUMMARY: As the U.K. government announces a £55 billion ($65.5 billion) program of tax hikes and spending cuts, the country faces its sharpest fall in living standards since records began.

TITLE: Biden administration will ask Supreme Court to allow student loan debt relief program to resume
SUMMARY: The Biden administration said it will ask the Supreme Court to lift an injunction and allow a major student loan debt relief program to resume.

TITLE: Nancy Pelosi to step down as House Democratic leader after two decades, with GOP set to take narrow majority
SUMMARY: Pelosi's announcement came shortly after Democrats were projected to narrowly lose their House majority to Republicans following the midterm elections.
